the national bunraku theatre (国立文楽劇場 kokuritsu bunraku gekijō) is a complex consisting of two halls and an exhibition room, located in chūō-ku, osaka, japan. the complex was opened in 1984 as the fourth national theatre of the country, to become the headquarters of bunraku. the japan arts council, an independent administrative institution of the ministry of education, culture, sports, science and technology, operates the national theatre.